     <TD BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TEXTAREA NAME="message" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Here is a powerleveling tip for low-to-mid levels: the weakest NPC class in all of Norrath is Bards because they can't use their songs (supposedly would be too difficult to code them not to hurt other NPCs with area effect spells and such), therefore at lower levels you can usually solo white/black and even yellow Bards. Of course, the problem with this approach is that it will make Bards throughout Norrath dislike you and make your life miserable down the road, not to mention the roleplaying aspects of killing good NPCs.

Luckily for you, there are a couple of level 12 Bard Sirens (makes sense when you think about it, right? :) in the Ocean of Tears. With Harmony, you should be able to easily pull one to a nearby island and dispatch it with alacrity. First, go to Kaladim and get a bind there. Then go to the docks in Butcherblock and take the Freeport boat. As soon as the boat zones into the Ocean of Tears, start paying attention. There will be some islands to the left with a few Aqua Goblins on them (high green - low blue to you) and then islands on the right with two Sirens and an Aqua Goblin at the top of the island. The latter one is what you want. The Sirens are non-agro, just beach there and say 'Hi!' to them. Buff yourself, Harmony the one that you don't want, porcupine and pull the other one to the next island. You will have just enough time to med to full and pull the second one to the your base before the first one repops. Rinse and repeat.

A few things to keep in mind. First, these Sirens have no faction hits associated with them (at least as of one year ago when I did them), but the Sirens on a nearby island do. Also, that other island is very dangerous since red dragoons spawn there at night and a red Troll swims around the island at most times. Don't go there. Second, the loot is poor, usually a few silver pieces and occasional Siren scales or something similarly named. The latter are a Magician quest item, look it up on the Web and you may be able to sell it to 30ish Magicians for a few plat and save them a camp in the OOT.

Not saying this is the best place at level 12, especially if you like to group, but if you want to get to lvl 14 fast, it will do the trick in a day or two :)

_________________
Muon/Gluon/Barion on E'ci</TEXTAREA></TD>
</TR>
